    • nextASCIIChar

      public abstract char nextASCIIChar()
      Pseudorandomly picks a printing ASCII character. The space is considered printing, the tab is not.
      Returns:
      An ASCII character. For example, 'm'.

    • nextASCIICharSeq

      public abstract String nextASCIICharSeq(int length)
      Gives a pseudorandom sequence of printing ASCII characters of a specified length.
      Parameters:
      length - How long the sequence of ASCII characters should be. Should not be negative. May be 0, but there's not much point to that. For example, 7.
      Returns:
      A pseudorandom String with length ASCII characters. For example, "t.lm8Qinvalid input: '<'".
      Throws:
      NegativeArraySizeException - If length is negative.

    • nextASCIICharSeq

      public abstract String nextASCIICharSeq(int minLength, int maxLength)
      Gives a pseudorandom sequence of printing ASCII characters.
      Parameters:
      minLength - The minimum length of the sequence. May be 0 but must not be negative. Must not be greater than maxLength. For example, 3.
      maxLength - The maximum length of the sequence. Must not be less than minLength. For example, 7.
      Returns:
      A sequence of printing ASCII characters of at least minLength but not more than maxLength. For example, "_aZ6WW".
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If either minLength or maxLength is negative, or if the former is greater than the latter.
